name: High Desert Psychological Services
review_text:
If your child needs help with ADHD, I suggest going elsewhere .  You  will wait several months for testing. I asked several times how long it would be and never got a straight answer. It has been a few months and we still waiting. I told them he was previously diagnosed and that I have the diagnosis on paper. They still have not helped him and seem to want to do their own testing, which makes no sense to me. He wanted help so that he could focus on  his schoolwork.  The school year is now over.
If you have a busy schedule and would like a set appointment time that is the same time each week with a therapist, forget about it. Instead if setting aside a day and time, they schedule it after each visit. You won‚Äôt get the same time slot and may have to wait longer than you‚Äôd  like. They do have a waitlist though incase someone cancels, in which case they will get you in sooner .  After each visit,  you will be asked to complete a review. Every time. I know that isn‚Äôt uncommon but I find it a little annoying.
The office staff is friendly and they do offer snacks but what good is that when you can‚Äôt get the help you need?
